    "author_association": "NONE",
    "body": "### Problem\n\n`:syntax off` ignored by the editor when in a default, out-of-the-box-state in:\n\n```\nNVIM v0.10.2\nBuild type: Release\nLuaJIT 2.1.1713484068\n```\n\n\n### Steps to reproduce\n\n1) Remove every  neovim configuration file so it is 100% stock ensuring there is no /usr/local config as well\n2) Create a `~/.config/nvim/init.lua` file that contains a highlight-able token:\n```\nvim.opt.background = \"light\"\n```\nNote the string highlighting.\n3) Restart neovim\n4) `:syntax off`, observe the highlight is still enabled\n\nIf you load this file in vim9 with no `~/.vimrc` and perform the same actions, it will disable the automatic syntax highlighting\n\n### Expected behavior\n\nSyntax highlighting should be disabled\n\n### Nvim version (nvim -v)\n\nNVIM v0.10.2\n\n### Vim (not Nvim) behaves the same?\n\nno, VIM - Vi IMproved 9.0 (2022 Jun 28, compiled May 04 2023 10:24:44)\n\n### Operating system/version\n\nLinux 6.1.0-27-amd64, Debian 12\n\n### Terminal name/version\n\nalacritty 0.14.0 (22a44757)\n\n### $TERM environment variable\n\nscreen-256color\n\n### Installation\n\nbuild from repo",
