            "body": "@clason \n\n```\nprintf '#include<stdio.h>\\n\\nvoid main() {\\n\\tprintf(\"hello\\\\n\");\\n }' > ./hello.c; nvim --clean ./hello.c\n```\n\nproduces:\n![Image](https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/d0c0c7d8-a35d-44bf-8d7d-fc2493dfcfd0)\n\nSome literals and strings are green. I can't turn this off in v0.10.2 with `:syntax off` as I can in v0.9.2:\n\n![Image](https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/a6628d86-8b60-4db8-8ebd-88debb5b30b6)\n\nI'm not sure that this is related to treesitter as the treesitter command given has no effect.\n\nNot that I want to lose the LSP for completion and definitions, I just don't want any syntax highlighting\n\n\n\n",
